snippet.textDisplay:
Lesson learned: sometimes it pays to complain about the useless stuff.


I work at a Walmart and I bought one of those Arcade 1Up arcade cabinets for $50 that we put in the breakroom after their popularity died down. Because it was used I had to get new joysticks. I went to their website to order more and the only option they had for shipping was $15 express shipping. I was like, "I understand they want to get me these joysticks as fast as possible, but it's not imperative to my life and my health that I get these joysticks for this cabinet within 2 days. Of course, that option is and should be available for people who want them that fast, but I am but a lonely retail worker who doesn't make a lot of money. I don't want to spend my entire lunch budget on these recreational materials. One could say I'm a little perturbed by this. A little mad, even." So I emailed them about my concerns and they refunded me 50% of the shipping cost. Neat!
